Amiga Sponsorship at the Commonwealth Games 98

@{ub}@{jleft}From: Chiew Sin Kwang, Managing Director Innovations Lights & Magic

AMIGA International, Inc. sponsored 32 bare AMIGA A1200 with 170Mb Hard 
disk in the even to make AMIGAs presence in Malaysia and the rest of the
world more noticeable. The 32 units of AMIGA A1200 were used extensively
during the Commonwealth Games 98 in Kuala Lumpur (September 11, 1998 to 
September 25, 1998) as information display system. Not only that the AMIGA
was used for information display to the public, it was also used to help 
raise funds for the Malaysian AIDS Foundation project entitled "the FRIDGE"
and "World AIDS Day". 10 AMIGA A1200s were fitted with accelerator card as
some software requires more than 2Mb of RAM to run. 12 units were used to 
display only static advertisement in the public place such as the train 
stations and bus stations where 2Mb RAM is only needed. 8 units were used 
to static advertisement at several shopping complexes. 2 units were kept 
for standby/replacement units.

We displayed game information to the public and 3rd party advertisements 
using the 10 AMIGA A1200s which was fitted with the accelerator card. The 
response from the advertisers were not good due to the early economy crisis
which were suppose to happened after the Commonwealth Games 98. The purpose
of the usage of AMIGA was to reach the public out of the game zone. The AMIGA
were equipped with modems and relative software to do the display the infor-
mation.

There was a 24 hours information broadcast centre set up in our office to 
provide up to date information to the public. The entire project as only 
manned by 3 people. It was rather a great challenge to us but we manage to 
pull it through.

At the same time, we were using the AMIGA computers for some fund raising 
projects and promotions to several corporate clients such as the Keretapi 
Tanah Melayu Berhad a.k.a. KTMB (Malaysias Only Railway Company). Ever 
since the success of our project, we had been discussing the the KTMB for 
almost 1 - 2 years in the implementation of the AMIGAs in the train stations 
are Train Information System and Advertising too. The idea was accepted and 
now we are waiting for their audio video sponsor to provide all the necessary 
equipment and TV sets to be installed at the stations or halts.

The AMIGAs will be installed with accelerator cards and modem to update latest
information. We will be conducting the full scale test run at 6 different 
location within a 100 km - 150 km radius. It the project is successful, we 
will be looking at about more that 30-50 units installed at other stations or
halts. Currently, the AMIGAs are used to do the trial run of the network infor-
mation system in our office.

Update after the sponsorship
From Innovations Lights & Magic (M) Sdn Bhd

We have been approached by a company which has the only license in Malaysia 
to do data broadcasting via Radio Frequency (RF) after our success in creating
a information network during the Commonwealth Games 98. We were asked to do 
Research and Development in using the AMIGA with their RDS system to display 
information on the TV rather on the LED board. One of the decoder was plugged 
into the AMIGAs serial port and immediately without any drivers, the AMIGA 
can interpret the information coming in. By using the Arexx and Scala Multi-
media MM300 software we manage to overcome their 80 characters data broadcast 
limitation to an unlimited length of text information. The AMIGA can be 
controlled to display certain information at certain time by just a few simple
commands on the PC. A radius of 100km was tested and proved to be successful 
and the information transfer via RF depends on the weather and location. 
Currently, the company is running into some financial difficulties and the 
project is on hold.

We were also approach by a Electronic Bill Board manufacturer in Malaysia to 
do animation and information display system which can play back on their 
gigantic billboard using LED display. The AMIGA worked very well with their 
gigantic billboard. The project was on hold due to some financial difficulties 
faced in the company.

Our company was on hold from 1st November 1998 to 12th April 1999 due to my 
unfortunate sickness. I was supposed to report to Petro about the update of 
the AMIGA Sponsorship but I could not get the original report from the Common-
wealth Games 98 committee.

Business has been resumed on the 13th April 1999 and we hope to have AMIGA 
International Inc continuous support to Innovations Lights & Magic (M) Sdn Bhd.
We apologize for the late reply.

Should you have any further queries or questions, please do not hesitate to 
contact me at either +603 3331132 or +6012 2107888.

Yours truly,

Chiew Sin Kwang
Managing Director 
